  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">CA Appeal Health System Strengthen in Bombali district</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&#x2022;	Training and Capacity building of Community Structures Community Engagement and ownership. Training for partners and communities on Right Based Approach (RBA) focused on health issues. 
&#x2022;	 Social mobilization and community health and hygiene promotion for positive living.
&#x2022;	Collect, analyse and dissemination of clinic data in three Christian Aid supported health facilities in three chiefdoms in Bombali districts in the Northern Region. 
&#x2022;	CHS/Inclusion and Complaint Response Mechanism (CRM). Advocacy around rights; creating demand and ensuring the government takes responsibility for some of these aspects (i.e. water wells and solar lights need to be maintained</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&#x2022;	improvement and maintenance of materials/equipment in the rehabilitated PHUS
&#x2022;	improve routine supervision, monitoring &amp; out- reach to health facilities.
&#x2022;	prompt reporting of health cases for treatment thus reducing morbidity and mortality of preventable diseases. 
&#x2022;	improve communities understanding on CHS/CRM
&#x2022;	establish and maintain feedback mechanisms.	
&#x2022;	an effective health system and adequate funding to increase the country&#x2019;s expenditures on strengthening the health system 
&#x2022;	increasing public and community awareness</narrative>
  </description>
